canonical:
  title: 賀表
  author: 鄭沆
  language: lzh
  text: 三陽協泰實惟道長之辰萬物向榮玆見化生之德邇遐同慶蹈舞惟均中賀 皇帝以不世出之姿發大有爲之政陟禹之迹增萬里之輿圖行夏之時受三朝之王會自天有佑與物爲春臣僻守藩封敻遙朝▣莫預稱觴之列▣▣拱極之心
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀表
  author: 鄭沆
  language: lzh
  text: 三陽協泰。實惟道長之辰。萬物向榮。玆見化生之德。邇遐同慶。蹈舞惟均。中賀。 皇帝以不世出之姿。發大有爲之政。陟禹之迹。增萬里之輿圖。行夏之時。受三朝之王會。自天有佑。與物爲春。臣僻守藩封。敻遙朝▣。莫預稱觴之列。▣▣拱極之心。
korean:
  title: 하표
  author: 정항
  language: kor
  text: 삼양(三陽)이 협태(協泰)하니 실로 도(道)가 신장(伸長)하는 때요, 만물이 향영(向榮)하니, 이에 만물이 화생(化生)하는 덕을 보겠나이다. 가까운 곳이나 먼 곳이나 경사를 같이 하옵고 춤추고 기뻐함이 오직 고르나이다, 중하(中賀) 황제께서 불출세(不出世)의 웅자(雄姿)로서 대유위(大有爲)의 선정(善政)을 행하시어, 우왕(禹王)의 자취를 밝고 만 리의 판도(版圖)를 넓히시며 하(夏)나라의 역시(曆時)를 다시 행하여 삼조(三朝)의 왕회(王會)를 받으시니, 하늘로부터 복이 내리심에 만물과 함께 봄을 만드나이다. 신이 구석진 번봉(藩封)을 지켜 멀리 조(朝)□를 궐하여, 만년상(萬年觴)을 받드는 열(列)에 참예하지 못하나, 북두성(北斗星)을 향하는 마음은 오직□□하나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0360&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Congratulatory Memorial
  author: Jeong Hang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Three Positives harmonize in auspiciousness—truly this is the season when the Way extends its reach. The myriad things flourish toward splendor—thus we witness the virtue of transformation's generation. Near and far alike share in celebration, their dancing and joy in perfect accord.

    In the central tribute of praise: The Emperor, bearing the rare genius of one born but once in ages, advances the governance of great accomplishment. He traces the footsteps of King Yu, expanding the territory ten thousand miles in breadth. He revives the calendar of the Xia, receiving the royal assemblies of three dynasties. Blessed from Heaven, he creates spring together with all things. Though your servant keeps distant watch over a remote domain, far removed from court, unable to join the ranks raising cups in ten-thousand-year toasts, yet my heart turns toward the Northern Star with singular devotion.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Three Positives' (三陽) refer to the three positive principles in cosmological cycles, suggesting auspicious times.
  - key: ''
    value: King Yu (禹王) is the legendary founder of the Xia Dynasty, known for his virtue and mastery of hydraulic engineering.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Northern Star' (北斗星) is a traditional image for the ruler's authority and the subject's loyal orientation.
  - key: ''
    value: This appears to be a congratulatory memorial presented to a reigning monarch, expressing both the prosperity of the realm and the speaker's distant but devoted loyalty.
